    "created_at": "2016-09-19T09:34:03Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-19T09:34:03Z",
    "body": "As I can see, there is no way currently to turn a bitmap buffer into a `NativeImage` object as it only tries to decode PNG or JPEG buffers in `createFromBuffer`.\n\nWe could extend the capabilities of `nativeImage.createFromBuffer` to handle bitmap buffers, or add a different method like `createFromBitmap` to `NativeImage`. In the future frame subscription will emit a `NativeImage` object by default (maybe we could make it optionally available sooner) though.\n\nMaybe you could use offscreen rendering, because that emits `NativeImage` objects by default and much better performance-wise, especially if you want to create video from it.\n"
  },
