    "created_at": "2016-09-20T04:24:17Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-09-20T04:24:17Z",
    "body": "Using offscreen rendering did indeed satisfy my requirements. I'm able to pipe the frames to `ffmpeg` and it works great.\n\nI noticed a couple things however: using `image.toPNG` is much more expensive than `image.toJPEG`.\n\nAlso it seems `image.getBitmap` is definitely the fastest but I was unable to figure out a way to get that buffer into `ffmpeg` happily.\n\nI know that they are 32bit BGRA but setting `pix_fmt=bgra` didn't work. \n"
